description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Clinical Coordinator to the wave 3 and 4 of the Mental Health Support Teams (MHST&#39;s). Successful applicants will join the wider teams from earlier waves in setting up and establishing MHST&#39;s as part of the Access function within Cheshire&#39;s CAMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Clinical Coordinator you will manage day to day running of the service and support the Clinical Leads in service delivery. You will also provide supervision and clinical leadership for those in the team including the Education Mental Health Practitioners in training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would be particularly keen to interview practitioners with experience in providing clinical supervision in some of the other CYP IAPT therapeutic modalities such as Parenting or Systemic Family Therapy. Successful candidates must be able to demonstrate a high level of clinical skill and experience and show ability to work in multiagency setting, especially schools. Driving is an essential part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie Holt Clinical Lead for MHST&#39;s Email address sophie.holt1@nhs.net Telephone number 01244393200&lt;/p&gt;
